Successful introduction of CS to the surface of MTX/COOH-MSN can be confirmed by the FESEM and the TEM images of MTX/COOH-MSN and MTX/MSN/CS (Fig. 3
                        ). A perfect spherical morphology is observed for the as-prepared MTX/COOH-MSN with the uniform size (Fig. 3A), whereas a dense skin layer is observed on the surface of the spherical nanoparticles for the MTX/MSN/CS (Fig. 3B), which can be ascribed to the introduction of the CS layer. Similarly, the differences in the TEM images of the two samples also reveal the introduction of CS. As can be seen, the MTX/COOH-MSN exhibits a dark contrast due to the opaqueness of MSN (Fig. 3C), which can be tightly wrapped by the CS layer with a relatively bright contrast (Fig. 3D). Obviously, the transmittance of the interconnected CS chains is better than that of the solid MSN. The size distribution of the obtained MTX/MSN/CS is determined by dynamic light scattering (DLS), and the results are shown in Fig. 4
                        . As can be seen, the particle size of the MTX/MSN/CS is mainly located between ~300 and ~500 nm.
